The paper deals with the problem of word sense disambiguation (WSD) using complex network models. This problem is primarily studied in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL), which makes it the most likely category. The paper also employs machine learning techniques for pattern recognition, which falls under the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of complex networks for WSD also involves the analysis of semantic relationships between words, which can be considered as a form of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the suitability of bipartite network models for the problem, which can be seen as a form of graph theory (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method, which involves the use of learning algorithms, making it relevant to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
